@NODE "mail_1" " Re: #8000000B "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-23-01 11:06:32
Subject: @{b}Re: #8000000B@{ub}

Hi amorel

> I keep getting this guru for some odd unknown reason. In both blitz
> versions. The guru says "trying to read 68881/2 fpu opcodes on a
system
> without that fpu" I do have a 040 which has a different fpu, but I do
NOT
> use any fpu code whatsoever. This also seems to have started to happen
> when I started implementing saving a file to disk. If it happens it
mainly
> happens right or soon after saving a file. Not always though.

I don't suppose it always happens in the same place in your code? I
guess you've tried single stepping with the debugger?

As for that error message from the guru, it's obviously not that, since
the 040fpu can handle all 881/2 instructions (even if some of them need
to be emulated). Do you run cyber/oxypatcher?

I guess it could be something like a stack problem, where it gets
corrupted and returns to some random address. You could try commenting
out the contents of the save function and then adding them back bit by
bit to see where the problem lies.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

