It certainly should not crash when it is compiling, although I've never 
actually tried doing 2/0 in my code. Unless Blitz has some sort of forward 
thinking decision making to save you time (it crashes now instead of later 
;).

> reddubug error. And I`m such a great coder, so does anyone know a way to
> "awake" the debugger? ;-) 

The command "Stop" should bring the debugger into action. You have 
installed all the debugger libraries - IIRC there are three or four which 
are required, but they should be installed by the script?

