On 24-Nov-01, Thilo Köhler wrote:
C=Hello amorel

C=The acidlib file you sent me in your .lha
C=file - does it contain any patchlibs or is it
C=just taken from the original blitz2 archive ?

Yes I did not change anything, thus it is original.

C=How did you apply the gadtools fix form
C=david ? Did you just "overload" this lib,

I just ran the script that came with the archive. That did the job, afaik you
just doubleclick it and you don`t need to be in the same dir as where the
acidlibs are.

So the script fixes the acidlib gt library.

C=are identical, but I think david has changed
C=some commands.

Yes that`s why the script fixes the acidlibs.

I`d advice you to use OS functions as much as possible though. I`ve heard
Blitz` gadtools stuff is quite a mess and even the NCS is without annoying
bugs, for example it doesn`t want to scroll and auto update
listviews/sliders/scrollers.

