@NODE "mail_26" " Re: AmiBlitz 2 "
From: Bernd Roesch <berndroesch1@...>
Date: 11-15-01 20:02:19
Subject: @{b}Re: AmiBlitz 2@{ub}

The Source is uploaded to Aminet yesterday.

In the hope i must not program AB2 (AB2 i use as short word for Amiblitz2 the old is bb2)alone in the future

Because I developing it alone without betatester for my own use,it can never handled all milliards possible Codes that possible 

I need AB2 mainly for programming Bars&Pipes Plugins and Photogenics plugins
and i want bookmarks clickjump etc.
undo/folding is nice but the time/usability is not good for me
to do that    
   
The macro Problems are because AB2 need not the {} brakets so some terms without parameter can make problems
The reason wy i remove this is better compatibility with motorolas standard asm Code (PPC use lots of macros)and i am lazy
I check the problems and try to fix this

If someone have more time then i he can manage the Source and all fixes should send to him to have
only one version availible

What i done so far

dim larger 65536 i have working now with single dim
end d0 exit a basic program with a result in d0 



Libnum problems:All is the same as in Blitz2 and i see no easy way to enhance the 16 bit
Value for libs.(The first 8 bit are the libnum the second 8 bit are the instructionnum)
Keep in mind that since bum8 all libs in blitzlibs/systems or basic are not need because they are in acidlibs.I use the newest Version from AMinet in 1999.

The terminate crash i dont know how this happen ( I use OS3.5 on winuae and realamiga)
and i start and quit AB2 very often.

If someone can give me some hints would be nice (mungwall trash size or even better fix it) 

Keep in mind
Working together and the results get better 


This is a short FAQ i make

Quest:
 When you install the new libs like memlib.obj staticslib.obj 
 or varslib.obj
 Do you have to delete the old one (in blitzlibs:stystem) ?.


Answer:
 Newer Blitzbasic Version dont use this files in 
 blitzlibs/systems so this should not include in the 
 libman if you create deflibs
 To see if you have a new blitzbasic version look
 if you have the file acidlibs (Introduced in BUM8)
 If so the system dir is not need because all the files are in acidlibs
 When you create a new deflibs with libman you must 
 select all files in patchlibs  

 Load the newest acidlib file from Aminet (is from 1999)


Quest:
 I see no slider in the right bookmark window
Answer: 
 Increase in prefs label size to min 18 with topaz 8 font

Quest:
 On WINUAEJIT when runtimeerrorcheck is on ,programs run extreme slow
 What can i do ?
ANswer
 Try disable the JIT (cpu nocache) for now
 This is a JIT Problem because it flushes the cache every trap
 I try to fix this   

