@NODE "mail_29" " AMIBlitz : The featuresI want to had "
From: visionfx <visionfx@...>
Date: 11-19-01 13:46:47
Subject: @{b}AMIBlitz : The featuresI want to had@{ub}

Hi Bernd, and others users,

The features that I want to had to a new AmiBlitz version are : ( Not all coded... but together we can add )
     For the compiler:
          a) New OS Commands descriptions in the source to validate the version library we will need
              instead of always 0
                 Ex: The user call the functions OpenScreenTagsList()  => Compiler look for version 36
                       The user call the functions AllocScreenBuffer()      =>  Update the version to 39
          
          b) More commands that are describe as Macro in Amiga Includes, ex:
                 1) UBYTE, UWORD, ULONG
                 2) NewList
                 3) The Method... DoSuperMethod, DoMetod etc... the enable the possibility to make new BOOPSI 

          c) Extend the maximum userlibs to 65535

          d) Include 020+/040/060 and FPU Asm opcode in the source table

          e) Re-write the branch routine to enable the short jump as BCC.b instead of only BCC.w ( 2 bytes less on every short branch )

          f) The possibility to tell on new command descriptions on witch register you want your data, instead of d0,d1,d2, etc..
                  Ex: !afunction{ #word }
                        !args       { #word,#long, #long }
                        !REGS    { #D2, #A1, #SP }                 <- that's what I want to had
                        etc...
                        This will increase the speed with a lot significiant time because the source is for now...
                              MOVE.w   Var_01(A5),D0
                              MOVE.l     Var_02(A5),D1
                              MOVE.l     Var_03(A5),D2
                             
                              etc... And you have to retake the value in each registers to transfert in the good one...

                        Will become,
                              MOVE.w   Var_01(A5),D2
                              MOVEA.l  Var_02(A5),A1
                              etc...


          Plus all users new ideals...

         Roger Beausoleil











                         
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_30" " Re: AMIBlitz : The featuresI want to had "
From: Bernd Roesch <berndroesch1@...>
Date: 11-19-01 16:06:04
Subject: @{b}Re: AMIBlitz : The featuresI want to had@{ub}


What I maybee add is AB2 registervalues.So you can theoretic write Progs in AB2 with same Speed as Assembler so noone need  write in Assembler:
for Ex
Reserve 4;reserve register d3-d7 as basic vars 
Basic Terms a*b+c need 2 regs (d0-d1)
Basic Terms a+b*c need 3 regs d0-d2
If a term want more than 4 registers AB2 give then the messsage formula too complex
Main reason for this is you can add constants etc in registers and must not load every time
_d6=xscale
_d5=yscale
_d4=zscale
_d3=coords
loop
destx(i)=_d6*coordx(i)     muls d6,d0
                                     ...........
desty(i)=_d5*coordy(i)     muls d5,d0
                                     ...........
destz(i)=_d4*coordz(i)     muls d4,d0
                                     ...........
 _d3=_d3-1                    ;sub.l #1,d3
if _d3>0 goto loop          cmp.l #0,d3
                                    bgt loop

Support 68k Adressing Modes is not important because JIT always convert it to risc instructions
I think implementing it is not too hard and the speedup is great in loops so i maybee try it

a main wantet feature from me is to remove the mem alloc in functioncalls with local variables.
Any suggestions how we can do this ?

