> a main wantet feature from me is to remove the mem alloc in 
> functioncalls with local variables.
>
> Any suggestions how we can do this ?
>
Use stack. And when debug enabled produce stack watching code to prevent 
stack overflows. (it needs to make necessary stack swaps, if the stack 
runs out)
This also needs change to the initialization code of the program, 
because the stack size will depend the amount of function calls. It 
would be cool to have the debug runing to determine the maximum amount 
of used stack, so that it could be used as a key value to the used 
amount in the initialization stack swap. This with optimized register 
storing/restoring in function call procedure would make function calls 
as fast as in C.
If the direct register parameter passing would be implemented, then it 
would be exactly like in C.




