@NODE "mail_34" " AmiBlitz compiled prog sizes "
From: Demon Hell <demonhell_@...>
Date: 11-15-01 16:15:10
Subject: @{b}AmiBlitz compiled prog sizes@{ub}


After spending ages getting the new AmiBlitz to even compile simple programs 
after gawd knows how many libnum clashes I got it to compile stuff.

I compiled the source of the mhi player using both std Blitz and the new 
AmiBlitz, and couldnt believe the diff in size.
Sure, It compiles a lot quicker, but the AmiBlitz compiled prog came out at 
just over 50kb, whereas the std blitz prog came out at just under 30kb.

Looking at the AmiBlitz compiled version in a hex editor, I noticed that 
there were great big (several kb) chunks of blank space (0`s) in the 
compiled code.

Has anyone else noticed this ?

