@NODE "mail_42" " AmiBlitz Speed "
From: Thilo Köhler <koehlerthilo@...>
Date: 11-17-01 15:25:20
Subject: @{b}AmiBlitz Speed@{ub}

Hi All!

Just some "Benchmarks":

Same Sourcecode, same Deflibs, Sourcecode size
~500KB, spitted in about 15 incude files, no debugger,
only one pass.
Machine was 68060 50 Mhz.

BlitzBasic2.1 : 35 sec
AmiBlitz: 4 sec

I would say wow, big speed improvement.
Compiled to .exe file the size is about 550KB,
also i noticed that the executable from AmiBlitz 
is slighly smaller (about 1 KB), but not bigger.

BTW. The SuperTed in AmiBlitz archive has version 2.2,
before mine was 2.52. Which one I should use ?
(and do I have to rename it to "PED" then ?)

Ciao,

Thilo


---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

