@NODE "mail_49" " Re: AmiBlitz2 "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-15-01 18:37:29
Subject: @{b}Re: AmiBlitz2@{ub}

Hi Thilo

> 2) BlitzLibMan from Amorel says "Can`t open acidlibs - check path!"

Have you got the Blitz2: assign pointing to your new directory
structure? Do you have an acidlibs file, or do all the libraries go into
one big deflibs?

> 3) I had to change some things in my source e.g.
> a mod 10            has to be
> a = a mod 10
> now. Error message was "Duplicate Label" - strange.

The duplicate label error is probably due to the changes made to the
label usage - you do not need to have a : after the label, so I guess in
the code you mention above, it thinks a is a label.

