@NODE "mail_58" " Re: AmiBlitz2 & TagItem "
From: Thilo Köhler <koehlerthilo@...>
Date: 11-26-01 22:28:58
Subject: @{b}Re: AmiBlitz2 & TagItem@{ub}

Hello Jean-Marc

Seems that you have the same problems like me.
It is nearly impossible to make a larger programm
compile correctly under AmiBlitz if you have
started it in Blitz2.

"Maximum <objcet> is trashed,
"used <object>" - commands report wrong numbers
and problems with spaces.

The duplicate objects in the compiler options seem
to be a problem when you "overload" some libraries
that contain objects, like most of the libs in acidlibs.

Try to avoid lib-clashes and this should be gone
(at least in my case it helped)

Ciao,

Thilo


