 This is because you have the library load double
 (check with blitzlibman to find double libnums)
 ALso the bbgtlib in patchlibs is a double lib
 (which is needed because the bbgtlib in acidlibs is very buggy)
 So there are always two entries gtlists in the listbox.To change the
 maxvalue of such a object change both values(or only last).
 If you load the file again you see that only the first
 entry has the new value.Then it is ok

Of course the best way is making a new acidlibs but who knows if the sources
of the lib we have the newest versions ?The original Blitz2 Source i get is
blitz1.9 so i fear that the libraries also not the newest model
But if someone want to compile them all and test nice.

The acidlibs is a normal deflibs (create with libman)file which only contain
the files in system /basic

