Hello,

I just tested AmiBlitz2.2 and first, I have NO problems with any GT-gadgets
including GTShape-gadgets.

But I recognized problems with some functions from "cliargslib". The
function "NumPars" returns "1" even if no parameters were given and the
corresponding string contains always shit. If you give more than 1 argument,
the functions seem to work fine.

I also detected some problems with macros when using them to set
windowflags. The following does not work:
    Window 1,0,0,400,200,!WinTags|#20000,"",0,1
but the following line works:
    Window 1,0,0,400,200,#20000|!WinTags,"",0,1

At least, I have still problems with the debugger (REDDebugger v2.52). If a
create a stand alone executable with debugger switched on, all works fine,
but a running program out of SuperTed stops when an error occurs and jumps
just back to the editor without any message !?

Regards,
Sven



