Hmm, what libnums have you guys had problems with? I checked the list of
free libraries (from the NCS archive) and if I got it correct, libnum
129 is free (used for one of the AmiBlitz libs) and 217 is the other it
uses and clashes with the ptreplaylib (or some such). The patchlibs
should not clash with anything, as these were originally Acid libraries
- nothing should clash with those (except the original Acid ones which
you would replace anyway).

I do have problems with the new compiler though:

DEFTYPE.l retval : retval = 0

No longer works. And that put me off trying to fix anything else :)
The new labels window kicks ass, even if for some reason it ends up
behind the main source window at startup.

Sven, do you still have the same quitting problems with the debugger on
the old version of Blitz?

---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_73" " Re: AmiBlitz2.2 "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-15-01 18:57:15
Subject: @{b}Re: AmiBlitz2.2@{ub}

Hi Thilo

> I though AmiBlitz needs the new libraries, is
> this right ?

I installed all the libraries and didn't have any problems with
libraries numbers clashing or things like that. The only problems I get
are with the actual compiler.

What I done was use the changelib tool (you can find it in the BlitzFix
and BlitzGTFix archives on Aminet, and there is also another tool for
doing the same thing in the BSS archive/CD/floppies) to update the
patchlibs and then copy the userlibs to my blitzlibs:userlibs/ and call
makedeflibs. So in a CLI, it went like this (IIRC):

lha x Amiblitz2.2.lha ram:
cd ram:amiblitz2/blitzlibs/patchlibs
changelib progdir: XXXX
cd /
copy userlibs/#? blitzlibs:userlibs
makedeflibs


the XXXX is the library file, and I used the changelib line for each
library (not the bbgtlib or the staticslib though ;). I use Blitz v2.1
(which is the one that has the acidlibs file), although AmiBlitz should
use whatever it needs.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

