Would it be possible to use ASCII as the default savemode and then have
an option for saving it in BB2 format? The ASCII source can be loaded by
all versions of Blitz, so there is no compatibility lost.

Renumbering tokens when loading sounds like a good idea, as it should
stop a lot of problems - it may be wise to keep some data for the tokens
for which library number it originally was part of (for being able to
load and save BB2 format source).

> 2.)We can use the old Macro brackets and label : so campatibility
should
> increase and the new style is switch on with optimize 128

That sounds like a good idea.

