@NODE "mail_95" " An idea for screen/window/gadget usage "
From: Barnaky Miklós <barnaky@...>
Date: 11-23-01 19:09:20
Subject: @{b}An idea for screen/window/gadget usage@{ub}


>Sorry, to use the GTGadPtr(0,1,1) you need to use my updated gtlib.
I will so, thanks! (Guess you mean the one named blitzgtfix.lha)

Hi for all out there!

Now things turned to 'much more complicated' - as allways when I sit
right face to face with coding :) - and there are a few points
to be confirmed.

To avoid to be confused by all things that must be counted at a 'simple'
window/gadget usage (bordersize, fontsize, etc) I want to declare a
so-called 'Global Screen Environment Variable' named eg. GSEV (it's on
my mind only this time but I'm starting to describe it). I imagined a
form like this:

--- cut here ---

NEWTYPE.GSEV
  wtb.w ; window top border
  wbb.w ; window bottom border
  wlb.w ; window left border
  wtb.w ; window right border
  wfw.b ; window font with
  wfh.b ; window font height
End NEWTYPE
DEFTYPE.GSEV TheScreen

Function.b A_Screen{<screen's parameter>}
  Shared TheScreen
  Screen <parameters>
  *scr._Screen=Peek.l(Addr Screen(SN))
  wtb=scr\WBorderTop + ... <the font size + 1, don't remember the form>
  <set other values>
End Function

--- cut here ---

The point to make it against the one in Amigalibs.res to collect them in
one variable and it can be really up-to-date, eg. using Dave's function from
"Winborder.lha" can handle the system's scroll border and addign the font size
to top border they get the real current values.

Once this all will be written in an include file it will be enough just
replace the line 'Screen ...' with this function and all window/gadget/etc
parameters have form like X+TheScreen\wlb,y+TheScreen\wtb, and so on.

Additionaly this can be expanded to 'handle' the public screen usage too; I
didn't decide yet if these must be two separated thing, one file with CNIF
macros to choose or a parameter/tag controlled choice to open a new screen
or use a public one. For this I wanna gather full specification to know which
one is better.

Sorry for this wild brain-attack, but I'd really like to know your opinions
about
this; is it worth to make and if so then which kind of datas should - or
sould _not_ - be included.

Yours

Barnaky Miklós
AKA Walter


*   *   *

Barnaky Miklós
Tel: 463-3878, E-mail: kol@...


