@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_96" " Re: An idea for screen/window/gadget usage "
From: amorel <amorel@...>
Date: 11-23-01 22:33:50
Subject: @{b}Re: An idea for screen/window/gadget usage@{ub}

On 23-Nov-01, Barnaky Miklós wrote:

C=my mind only this time but I'm starting to describe it). I imagined a
C=form like this:

C=--- cut here ---

C=this; is it worth to make and if so then which kind of datas should - or
C=sould _not_ - be included.

Using font sensitivity is not just a matter of how high it is and adjusting
accordingly. There`s also a thing called proportional fonts. I use this os
function to find the size of a certain string(perhaps the longest text string
in a bunch of grouped gtgadgets which need the same dimensions) and add it to
the initial size:

TextExtent_ *scr\RastPort,&tempstr$,1,textvalues.TextExtent

*scr Is a pointer of type .Screen to your screen, or if not yet intialised, to
the workbench screen(found with lockpubscreen_ unlockpubscreen_ commands),
&tempstr$ is the string you use(and & to give the address) and 1 is the size
of the string(1 character in this case), the last parameter is where the
values will be returned. Check the rkrm for a complete description of these
commands. It`s really handy to use with any font.

Regards

