@NODE "mail_104" " Re: asl.library "
From: amorel <amorel@...>
Date: 11-24-01 23:17:36
Subject: @{b}Re: asl.library@{ub}

On 24-Nov-01, Steve Hargreaves wrote:

C=req.FileRequester=AllocAslRequest_(#ASL_FileRequest,0)
C=if req
C=    succ=ASLRequest_(req,#ASLFR_DrawersOnly,True)

C=etc. etc.

C=However, It won't compile. Keeps coming back with a "Can't assign
expression"
C=error.

C=Anybody help?

Yeah, req.FileRequester needs to be *req.FileRequester a pointer so to say,
many OS functions return a pointer.

Also it`s best to use an array for tags. You can even use NCS tag support for
that. But I`ll show the other way.

*req.FileRequester=AllocAslRequest_(#ASL_FileRequest,0)
if *req
    dim tags.TagItem(2)
      tags(0)\ti_Tag=#ASLFR_Drawersonly,true
      tags(1)\ti_tag=#TAG_END
    succ=ASLRequest_0(*req,&tags(0))

Notice the &tags(0) as other os functions like openwindowtaglist_ take tags(0)
as argument, thus without the &.

Regards

-- 
