@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_105" " Re: asl.library "
From: amorel <amorel@...>
Date: 11-25-01 03:04:27
Subject: @{b}Re: asl.library@{ub}

On 24-Nov-01, Steve Hargreaves wrote:

C=This doesn't

C=asltit$="Choose a path":aslpath$="Sys:"
C=InitTagList 1,1
C=Use TagList 1
C=AddTags 1,#ASLFR_DrawersOnly,True
C=AddTags 1,#ASLFR_TitleText,&asltit$
C=#AddTags 1,#ASLFR_InitialDrawer,&aslpath$#
C=  npath$="": aslpath$="":tpth$=""
C=  *req.FileRequester=AllocAslRequest_(#ASL_FileRequest,TagList(1))
C=  If *req
C=    succ=AslRequest_(*req,TagList(1))
C=    npath$=Peek$(*req\fr_Drawer)
C=    FreeAslRequest_(*req)
C=  EndIf  

C=When I run the prog with the #ASLFR_InitialDrawer tag set, it crashes when I
C=try
C=and open the ASL requester, but not without. (It's not just the prog that
C=crashes, either, it tales the whole system with it)

C=Any ideas?

Well yes ;-)
You set aslpath$="" but before you set it to "Sys:" I assume you want "Sys:"
to appear in your aslrequest as the initial drawer. You provide the address of
the string you set, which is how it`s supposed go, but then do NOT change that
string. The string is NOT copied into the aslrequest tags but it only has a
pointer. So when you change the string it also changes in the taglist.

Remove the aslpath$="" and it should work. Though, giving null as
initialdrawer shouldn`t cause a crash.

Regards

-- 
-*AMOREL*- musician/programmer     \ \ Amiga 1200T/PPC/040/32/6g more shit
http://www.xs4all.nl/~amorel        \ \ Good old C=64 and an attitude!
