@NODE "mail_126" " Re: Can someone check this please? "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-28-01 18:36:28
Subject: @{b}Re: Can someone check this please?@{ub}

Hi Thilo

> >> I want to install it. I had it installed some time ago and 
> >> I remember it was quite good. (and I think it had this feature
> >> to look at the structures)
> > OK, thanks.
> ...but I`m not sure.

John Mason confirmed it :)

> >> BTW: Why it seems that I`m the only one who has
> >> really big problems with picasso96 ?

> > I thought you got this fixed when you used my patch for the
debugger? Or
> > do you mean any program which uses VWait?

> Yes, I got it fixed,

Ah, OK, so it was a general question. You are not the only one who has
these slowdown problems with P96. Some P96 graphics card drivers are not
capable of producing interrupts for vertical blanks (=top of frame) -
personally I get problems with WinUAE and the Mediator/Voodoo3 drivers
(when the M/V3 drivers have interrupts turned off).

VWait uses the WaitTOF_ OS call which usually puts an application to
sleep until the OS gets an interrupt for the vertical blank. But the P96
driver either immediately does a busy-wait loop and polls the scanline
position or it does not wait at all (I can never remember :).

Either way, it ends up slowing the system down.

I'm not sure if CGFX suffers from this problems, as I have never used
it.

> but I`m wondering what will happen if I install the LESDebugger. It
> takes too much time for me to do installation stuff (backups, change
> deflibs, install debugger, testing etc.). I need a working
> installation for my developements. That`s because I switched back to
> old blitz2 (not to amiblitz, it made too much trouble).

Well, if the REDDebugger is working OK I suggest you leave it as it is -
the LESDebugger is nearly the same. If you really want to change back to
the LESDebugger, you should make a backup of your current Blitz setup so
you can easily go back if needed.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

