@NODE "mail_129" " CD notification again "
From: Demon Hell <demonhell_@...>
Date: 11-21-01 17:29:38
Subject: @{b}CD notification again@{ub}

Grrr, it`s no good whatever I do Blitz just wont compile my program with the 
asm in it (either inline or "include") :(

Seems like the asm I`m leeching uses some constants I can`t find anywhere!

Below is the original asm from medianotify off aminet.
Specifically, blitz doesnt like the (sp)-, (sp)+ and _signal .
Anyone got any ideas?

AFAIK the code will be called by the OS itself, so I dunno if there are any 
major changes that need doing to it.

INCLUDE	"exec/types.i"
	SECTION IRQCODE,CODE
	XDEF	@ChangeNotifier
	XREF	_signal

@ChangeNotifier:
	move.l	a0,-(sp)	; cpu register a1 contains a pointer to the task to be 
signalled
	moveq	#0,d0
	move.l	_signal,d1
	bset	d1,d0
	jsr	-324(a6)	; Signal()
	move.l	(sp)+,d0
	rts
	END


_________________________________________________________________
