---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_130" " Re: CD notification again "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-21-01 17:38:46
Subject: @{b}Re: CD notification again@{ub}

Hi Demon

> INCLUDE	"exec/types.i"
>  SECTION IRQCODE,CODE
>  XDEF	@ChangeNotifier
>  XREF	_signal

Remove all that. You should use amigalibs.res to get the include. The
other stuff is for specifying using this as code (section), and
specifying access to _signal as an external symbol (variables/label - in
another source file), and telling the assembler to make @ChangeNotifier
available to other source files.

Here's the "fixed" code ;) :

ChangeNotifier:
 move.l	a0,-(a7)	; cpu register a1 contains a pointer to the task
to be signalled
 moveq	#0,d0
 move.l	_signal,d1
 bset	d1,d0
 jsr	-324(a6)	; Signal()
 move.l	(a7)+,d0
 rts
_signal: ds.l 1

In your Blitz source, you should do a Poke.l ?_signal,<real signal
value> to set the value of the signal variable up for the ASM (the C
code probably just does 'signal=foo;').

---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

