@NODE "mail_138" " CD notification? "
From: Demon Hell <demonhell_@...>
Date: 11-21-01 00:50:58
Subject: @{b}CD notification?@{ub}

OK, I`m back with another problem that`s got me stumped.

I`m doing a CLI based CD player, and basically need either a message or a 
signal from the OS when the CD is ejected/closed/diskchange etc.
Cos it`s CLI based, I can`t (AFAIK) use IDCMP to give me a diskchange event.

I started thumbing through the RKRM`s, and found the startnotify 
command..tried that, but it don`t like CD ROMS for some reason(even the demo 
executable on the Amiga Dev CD fails), so it looks like thats outta the 
question too :(

Groping about aminet, I found an archive called medianotify.lha (in 
disk/misc) that has some C source and it works !!
Unfortunatly, this code has a small snippet of asm, which is passed to the 
OS as an interrupt to be used in an IOrequest.
Anyway, not being well up on ASM, I just cut and pasted the asm code into 
blitz but it choked on it :(

So, does anyone have any better ideas of how to get a diskchange signal from 
the OS, or know howto get the above asm working?
TIA
DemonHell

