@NODE "mail_157" " EsseErre: Blitz2 and AmiBlit2 "
From: Stefano Maria Regattin <stefano.regattin@...>
Date: 11-19-01 10:35:24
Subject: @{b}EsseErre: Blitz2 and AmiBlit2@{ub}

Date: Monday, 19th November 2001

Hi Amiga Blitz users!
I have a problem with Blitz2 and AmiBlitz2.
The problem is in the objects handling; selecting the COMPILER OPTIONS in Blitz2 I have a crash when I reach the CONSOLES object, that is the latest of the objects list.
With AmiBlitz2 only part of the objects are displayed: the first object is GTList instead of Anim of Blitz2; I see after the CONSOLES objects the objects S and TIONS (so is reported in the AmiBlitz2 compiler options); seen all this, my emulated Amiga (WinUAE) crashes.
Yesterday all gone fine copying the ACIDLIBS from the ULTIMATE BLITZ CD; I  have done so because I have tried to patch Blitz2
by the  patches found onthe site http://www.blitz-2000.co.uk/, but the pacthes had no effect.
I have created a new DEFLIBS file with the command MAKEDEFLIBS, and now is sized over 600kiloBytes.
Is there anybody that have encountered a problem like mine?
Does Anybody solved this problem?
Many thanks and many greetings from Milan, Italy.

Ciao da
Stefano Maria Regattin
EsseErre Software Solutions
http://utenti.tripod.it/esseerre/Stefano.html
e-mail: esseerre@...
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_158" " Re: EsseErre: Blitz2 and AmiBlit2 "
From: Demon Hell <demonhell_@...>
Date: 11-20-01 00:21:21
Subject: @{b}Re: EsseErre: Blitz2 and AmiBlit2@{ub}

>The problem is in the objects handling; selecting the COMPILER OPTIONS >in 
>Blitz2 I have a crash when I reach the CONSOLES object, that is the >latest 
>of the objects list.
>With AmiBlitz2 only part of the objects are displayed: the first >object is 
>GTList instead of Anim of Blitz2

Do you mean that you type in Anim and it displays GTList instead?

>Yesterday all gone fine copying the ACIDLIBS from the ULTIMATE BLITZ >CD; I 
>  have done so because I have tried to patch Blitz2
>by the  patches found onthe site http://www.blitz-2000.co.uk/, but the 
> >pacthes had no effect.
>I have created a new DEFLIBS file with the command MAKEDEFLIBS, and >now is 
>sized over 600kiloBytes.

Sounds like the good old clashing library number problem again, and 
installing the libs from the CD probably just wrote over whichever ones were 
causing problems with the correct libnumber.
The patches do work, and are worth reinstalling as they fix several bugs and 
"features" within the libraries.
The only reason they wont work is if the library numbers clash, and then 
Blitz gets confused over what command it is supposed to be using.


