@NODE "mail_166" " Re: GTGetAttrs problem (and greetings to everyone!) "
From: David McMinn <dave@...>
Date: 11-16-01 22:29:55
Subject: @{b}Re: GTGetAttrs problem (and greetings to everyone!)@{ub}

Barnaky Miklós says the moon is made of cheese, but it's actually made of GTGetAttrs problem (and greetings to everyone!)

> Anyway, I'd like to get a GTListView's GTLV_Top tag to scroll it with
> keyboard (I mean: get the current value, change it on keyboard action
> and set it with GTGetAttrs,
> which one is works properly).

See the attached source for a workaround.

The problem is the GTGetAttrs
command searches through the gadget list for the first gadget with the  ID
you specify. Listviews are made up from a number of gadgets, and you
should really only use the pointer that gets returned when you create the
gadget, but the lib doesn't.

Bye
-- 
