movement during action
the MouseMove IDCMP flag must be seted; after some funny misstakes I
discovered that this code seems to work properly:

evn.l=WaitEvent
evq.l=EventQu... (you know...)
Select evn
   Case $10
      If GadgetHit=N and (evq and $8000)>0
         ; where N is the scroller's id
         gtsc=EventCode
      End If
End Select

But even if it's work I still can't be sure that it will do at any
situation. As
a matter of fact, I just watched all available values as I pulled the scroller
and that was the conlusion (GadgetHit keep the last used number while
evq seems to sign if the mouse move free or within a gadget action). Is
it a "legal way" (or at least really useable) or just accident?

And anyway: AddIDCMP $10 makes to get message at mouse move, but
still there must be a method to get the srcoller value; or are we
back again at GTGetAttrs?

That's all for now, let's have a good day!

Barnaky Miklós
AKA: Walter

