@NODE "mail_175" " Re: GTGetAttrs problem (and greetings to everyone!) "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-20-01 16:11:58
Subject: @{b}Re: GTGetAttrs problem (and greetings to everyone!)@{ub}

Hi Barnaky

> It must be my fault, but the source "GTGetAttrs" failed
> for me; 1st I got an error message, then I found to change
> "GTGadPtr(0,1,1)" into "GTGadPtr(0,1)" can solve it, but

Sorry, to use the GTGadPtr(0,1,1) you need to use my updated gtlib. The
problem with GTGetAttrs remains the same for any version of the gtlib
though, and I have already explained why that doesn't work for scrollers
(listviews and sliders too).

> The scroller-case over (still funy behaviors but it seems
> to be fixable with your last code), but I'd like to see
> your point about

> > scroller_down.w=0
> > AddIDCMP #SCROLLER_IDCMP
> > ...
> 1. Is there a reason to define it exactly as word?

No, but I prefer to define my variables at a specific type. You can make
it anything you want, as long as you can store 0 and 1 in it :)

> 2. What #SCROLLER_IDCMP is for? I mean: is there a function
>    of it in this example?

#SCROLLER_IDCMP is a set of IDCMP flags that scroller gadgets use (you
can find lists of these for each type of gadget in
libraries/gadtools.h). Generally speaking, if you add all the IDCMP
flags for all the different types of gadgets you use in that window,
then it should be set up correctly for reciving all the IDCMP messages
for your gadgets.

 IIRC it is defined as
#IDCMP_GADGETDOWN|#IDCMP_MOUSEMOVE|#IDCMP_INTUITICKS|#IDCMP_GADGETUP.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

