@NODE "mail_185" " Re: IDCMP_GADGETHELP "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-30-01 13:29:29
Subject: @{b}Re: IDCMP_GADGETHELP@{ub}

Hi Thilo

> IDCMP_GADGETHELP is the right way (please correct me
> if I`m wrong) to do that. But I never get those messages.
> I think you have to create an ExtGadget, I`m not
> sure if the bbgtlib supports this.

Yes, it does (it's automatic actually - on OS3.0+ all gadtools gadgets
created with CreateGadget_ are automatically ExtGadgets).

You also need to use the *IAddress field of the IntuiMessage you recieve
- I do not think GadgetHit returns the correct values for gadgethelp
messages, but I could be wrong. You can use the EventIAddress (or maybe
EIAddress or IAddress) command to get the contents of the *IAddress
field at the most recent event.


