@NODE "mail_187" " Re: Image remapping "
From: Steve Hargreaves <Steve@...>
Date: 11-12-01 21:52:22
Subject: @{b}Re: Image remapping@{ub}

Hi there, John

On 12-Nov-01, you said:

JM>  Does anyone have a lib or an OS function that will remap an IFF brush to
JM> a given screen's colours?  I was planning to display the brush as a
JM> datatype, but it looks like I can't specify where in my window the image
JM> will appear?!  Now that I've written that I guess there must be a way to
JM> get an image to appear in a specific spot, but I don't know what it is! :)

There are a couple of options. 

i) Have a look on Aminet for the palette remap example (dev/basic - I can't
remember the archive name). I think it's also available on the Blitz-2000 site.
ii) Write your own using the ObtainBestPen_ OS routine.
iii) If your GUI is MUI, instead of using a brush, use an icon image, and the
newicon library to do the remapping (I had best results with this option).

If you decide to go for option 3, but are unsure how to proceed, mail me
privately, and I can let you have some code chunks.

Regards



Steve
