@NODE "mail_190" " Re: Installing AmiBlitz "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-22-01 10:24:36
Subject: @{b}Re: Installing AmiBlitz@{ub}

Hi Thilo

> 1) "Acidlibs" file contains all libs that where previously (before
2.0) in
> the "System" AND the "Basic" drawer. Right ?

Yes.

> 2) I should never produce libnums clashes, this includes no clashes
> with the libnums in the acidlibs. Right ?

Like Amorel says, Blitz will still run, but the compiler may get
confused between which commands you are trying to use.

> 3) I want to install AmiBlitz, but there are five libs (like
bbgtlib.obj)
> in the patch drawer, and I do have to install them. Right ?

You don't have to, but they fix some bugs. I would recommend installing
the following libraries (all should go into the acidlibs file):

memlib
varslib
staticslib (seems to be the same as Julian Kinraid's fix)

The reason for only installing these two are that there is already a
fixed (and I think more useful, but I cannot remember all the fixes)
asllib available from RWE and my bbgtlib is more useful.

You should also install the fpulib (IIRC the fpulib is definately
required) and wzlib.

> 4) All these libs produce clashes with the libnums in acidlibs. Right
?

Yes, since they are the same libraries that are in acidlibs.

> 5) So how can I install them ? They are already in the acidlibs file.
Do I
> have to split the acidlibfile again with a tool ? ...and remake one
big
> deflib file again ?

No, you can use the changelib tool which is included in the BBGTLib fix
by me, and the BlitzFix archive (fix by Julian Kinraid). There is also a
tool on the CD by RWE which does this.

> 6) Where can I find the newest acidlib file ?

The acidlibs file has not been changed for a long time. Chances are the
one from the CD is the newest, and then you apply the patches available.
Someone mentioned it was also on Aminet, but I've never looked for it.

Alternatively you could create your own one from the libraries in
'System' and 'Basic'. Move the userlibs/otherlibs/etc directories out of
Blitzlibs: and run makedeflibs. This will give you a deflibs which
contains only the system and basic libs. Rename that file to acidlibs.
Put the userlibs/otherlibs/etc drawers back into blitzlibs: and remove
the basic and system drawers.

> 7) The AmiBlitz archive contains a new bbgtlib.obj. I also installed
the
> famous GadTools fix. Is this fix included in the new lib from AmiBlitz
> archive ?

No.


---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

