> Do I have to split the acidlibfile again with a tool ? ...and remake one
> big deflib file again ?
>
> 6) Where can I find the newest acidlib file ?
>
> 7) The AmiBlitz archive contains a new bbgtlib.obj. I also installed the
> famous
> GadTools fix. Is this fix included in the new lib from AmiBlitz archive ?
>

User reportet that there are better bbgtlib.obj are out.Choose the
best and put it in the patchlib drawer.This way you can do with all libs and
patch so the libs in acidlibs

BTW If someone has time and fun to test and merge in to get a 100% perfect
bbgtlib is nice
          Please check also memtrashes.Many think its not important to lose
300 Bytes per winopen/close.But every close defrag memory because gadtools
left in Memory many 16bit chunks.
so memalloc/memfree get slower and slower because alloc mem must search long
in the list to get a size that match the requestet size
> That`s all for now.
>
> Ciao,
>
> Thilo
