Oggetto: LotanIO


> If you write a set of commands to write to a file, like for example
WriteNM to
> write numbers then you`d expect a command to do the opposite, that is
reading
> the number. Now it is a mystery to me why LotanIO does not have such a
> command. It does have ReadCH and ReadLN to read a character and a line of
> strings, but no ReadNM.
>
