@NODE "mail_203" " Menus "
From: amorel <amorel@...>
Date: 11-18-01 06:10:54
Subject: @{b}Menus@{ub}

A helpful person on irc managed to help me out(hey Kinners ;) with the menu
macros so I now think I have part of the solution. Part that is, because it
doesn`t seem to work correctly. I`ll paste the code here:

Case #IDCMP_MENUPICK
  menunumber=imsg9\Code

  While menunumber<>#MENUNULL
    *item=ItemAddress_(*menustripw9,menunumber)

    menunum=(menunumber & $1F) ;!MENUNUM menunumber
    itemnum=((menunumber LSR 5)& $003F) ;!ITEMNUM menunumber
    subnum=((menunumber LSR 11)& $001F) ;!SUBNUM menunumber

    Select menunum
      Case 0
        Select itemnum
          Case 5
           Gosub cleanend
        End Select
    End Select

    menunumber=*item\NextSelect
  Wend

What happens is that the case statements are not being satisfied(and that is
due to the fact menunum etc are not being read correctly). Also
menunumber(this and itemnum etc are a word) does never become #MENUNULL so the
loop will go on forever. This should not happen even though menunum and such
are not being read correctly, I`d say. For the rest I could not find any
errors in this code, thus pointers are of the correct type etc. And this is
also how it`s done in rkrm examples.

Anyone got an idea what`s wrong here?

Regards

-- 
-*AMOREL*- musician/programmer     \ \ Amiga 1200T/PPC/040/32/6g more shit
http://www.xs4all.nl/~amorel        \ \ Good old C=64 and an attitude!
Running QNX rtp, linux, AmigaOS      \ \  / /Half a decent studio
Music: www.mp3.com/vopak              \ \/ /Contact me for bookings,
www.xs4all.nl/~amorel/amusic.html      \/\/productions,demos,programs...

-*Now also plays Sid songs ----> Amoralplayer a no fuss audioplayer*-


---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_204" " Menus "
From: amorel <amorel@...>
Date: 11-19-01 02:00:21
Subject: @{b}Menus@{ub}

Well seems the problem has been solved, with the help of Kinners again ;-)
Adding "and $ffff" did the trick, as shown below. 

Case #IDCMP_MENUPICK
  menunumber=imsg9\Code AND $ffff

  While menunumber<>#MENUNULL
    *item=ItemAddress_(*menustripw9,menunumber)

    menunum=(menunumber & $1F) ;!MENUNUM menunumber
    itemnum=((menunumber LSR 5)& $003F) ;!ITEMNUM menunumber
    subnum=((menunumber LSR 11)& $001F) ;!SUBNUM menunumber

    Select menunum
      Case 0
        Select itemnum
          Case 5
           Gosub cleanend
        End Select
    End Select

    menunumber=*item\NextSelect AND $ffff
  Wend

Regards

-- 
-*AMOREL*- musician/programmer     \ \ Amiga 1200T/PPC/040/32/6g more shit
http://www.xs4all.nl/~amorel        \ \ Good old C=64 and an attitude!
Running QNX rtp, linux, AmigaOS      \ \  / /Half a decent studio
Music: www.mp3.com/vopak              \ \/ /Contact me for bookings,
www.xs4all.nl/~amorel/amusic.html      \/\/productions,demos,programs...

-*Now also plays Sid songs ----> Amoralplayer a no fuss audioplayer*-


---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

