@NODE "mail_215" " Re: MUI Problems "
From: Steve Hargreaves <Steve@...>
Date: 11-05-01 13:16:49
Subject: @{b}Re: MUI Problems@{ub}

Hi there, ditud@...

On 05-Nov-01, you said:

d> Another problem that I have is that my MUI window an be sized only in
d> horizontal dimension. I can't figure out why. In other examples windows can
d> be sized in any dimension. What do I have to do to change size of my window
d> in any dimension?

This is a bug with the MUILabel command in EFMUILib. The way around it is to
create your own label gadget, using the "Text.mui" class. eg, instead of using
MUILabel for a text label, use:-

lab$="Your text label string"
MUINewObject xx,"Text.mui",#MUIA_Text_Contents,&lab$

This will still create a text label as MUILabel, but will allow re-sizing in
both directions.

The bug only occurs in some circumstances (I think, when you use the lable as
part of an HGroup which itself is part of a VGroup) so you can use MUILabel
sometimes without problems.

Regards



Steve
