On 01-Nov-01, Lewis Brunton wrote:
C=Hi,

C=I there a command to make blitz pause for a specified amount of time? I.e. 5
C=secs.

There are many(I figure you mean a blitz compiled program). NVwait is
one(NVWAIT(50)) should wait 1 second on Pal systems. Delay_(microseconds) is
another and preferable method, as it is gfx card friendly and does wait for a
set amount of time, unlike vertical waits. Also you could use the timer
function. Check statfuncs on aminet/dev/basic/ which has a nice timer
function(I should know I ripped it for my program, yes I will credit ;-)

