---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_228" " Re: Picasso96 & InvertPixelArray "
From: David McMinn <dave@...>
Date: 11-07-01 11:12:49
Subject: @{b}Re: Picasso96 & InvertPixelArray@{ub}

Hi Thilo,

> Or any idea how to draw a vertical line in a window and
> remove it again without desroying the backgound ?
> I used two calls of InvertPixelArray() but this seems
> not to be a perfect idea.

Something like this:

Move_ RastPort(0),x,y
SetDrMd_ RastPort(0),#XOR ; Not sure about that constant
                          ; IIRC it's in graphics/rastport.h
Draw_ RastPort(0),x2,y2

Which should invert all the pixels in that line. Draw the same line again 
to get back to the original state (which sounds like what you are trying to 
do).

