@NODE "mail_233" " Re: Picasso96 & VWait "
From: amorel <amorel@...>
Date: 11-07-01 01:29:05
Subject: @{b}Re: Picasso96 & VWait@{ub}

On 06-Nov-01, Thilo Köhler wrote:

C=And how to put my program to sleep ? Bussy waiting is
C=not a good choice. I could do a "Wait_ (sigflag.l)
C=and put a "Signal_ sigflag.l"  into the VBlak interrupt.
C=But maybe there is another way to do this.

If you put it to sleep, that particular process or task can not do anything
else. So your screen only gets updated when it leaves the wait state as some
message/signal appears. Which happens ofcourse at far more irregular
intervals. Unless you have intuiticks going, but that`s only about 10 Hz afaik
and should not really be used that way as it`s not sure if any ticks will
arrive at certain times, it`s a kinda lose thing. Intuiticks is used for stuff
like scrolling a listview while mousebutton is being pressed on an arrow etc.

Regards

