> the system :(
I have heared about this problem, but its the same on emulators too.
BTW. using Cybergraphics instead of Picass96 there are no
problems.
 
Ciao,

Thilo


---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_239" " Re: Picasso96 & VWait "
From: Sami Näätänen <sami.naatanen@...>
Date: 11-07-01 02:17:00
Subject: @{b}Re: Picasso96 & VWait@{ub}

Thilo Köhler wrote:

>Hello Nick
>
>>Have you got a cybergfx card? that has serious problems with VWait as it's
>>not totally system friendly. It's a well known problem with the CV64's...
>>
>Yes I havea CyberVision64 3D, but its the same on WinUAE and Amithlon, 
>so better not to use it ...
> 
>
>>most cards wait for the system to send a message, but the cyber cards poll
>>the system :(
>>
>I have heared about this problem, but its the same on emulators too.
>BTW. using Cybergraphics instead of Picass96 there are no
>problems.
> 
>
If I remember correctly it had something to do with the structure of 
PicassoIV so that Picasso IV API provided only a routine that other 
cards have to busy wait or something like that.
Don't know for sure, but this CPU hoging seems to applie only to 
PicassoIV api, with other GFXboards than PicassoIV itself.
I think Picasso API uses WaiTBOF or similar, which can't be done without 
busy waiting the last scanline. (Except with native display using 
copperlist and interrupt ;)




