@NODE "mail_241" " Re: Picasso96 & VWait "
From: David McMinn <dave@...>
Date: 11-07-01 11:12:49
Subject: @{b}Re: Picasso96 & VWait@{ub}

Hi Thilo,

> So you should never use VWait, NVWait and WaitTOF_.
> All of them don`t work under Picasso96.

See Sami's explanation which is correct. Some combinations of card and 
graphics system do not generate interrupts at the top of the frame and so 
revert to polling the status of the scanline.

Personally I have seen it affect WinUAE and the Mediator/Voodoo3 with 
interrupts turned off.

> BTW. the Debugger freezes Picasso96 too.
> Is this gone with the RedDebugger ?

It is if you use the patch I made for it at my homepage :)

