@NODE "mail_245" " Possible fix of $1000000f bug "
From: Bernd Roesch <berndroesch1@...>
Date: 11-18-01 21:45:21
Subject: @{b}Possible fix of $1000000f bug@{ub}

I think this  is because of missing the file ted.menus in prefs/env-archive
Here is such a file.Copy it boot and try.Does this help ?

This is the content of this (If you use windows make sure notepad add no
.txt

Edit...,~,0,run >NIL: Blitz2:PlugIns/MenuED
~,~,0,~
Help...,~,2,run >NIL: Blitz2:RedHelp/RED_HELP LIB="%g" CMD="%t" PORT="%r"
SCREEN="%s"
Library Help...,~,3,run >NIL: Blitz2:RedHelp/RED_HELP LIB="%g" PORT="%r"
SCREEN="%s"
TEDDock,0,0,run >NIL: Blitz2:PlugIns/SuperTED/TEDDock
RedCalc,~,0,run Blitz2:plugins/superted/redcalc
Wizard,~,0,run >nil: h0:w-pr/StormWIZARD/StormWIZARD





















