@NODE "mail_250" " realtime.library "
From: Demon Hell <demonhell_@...>
Date: 11-25-01 00:50:06
Subject: @{b}realtime.library@{ub}

Ok, another head scratcher for you..(seeing as so many of you decided to 
stay in this weekend ;) )

I was looking through the RKRM`s again yesterday, trying to find a nice easy 
way to get a signal at 1 sec intervals (without resorting to interrupts). 
And stumbled across the realtime.library..

  Anyway, to make a long story even longer, I can make the damn thing gimme 
a signal for the first second..after that, silence.
This is with the metronome flag set, and the pl_Conductor flag set as per 
the autodocs.
  Although it doesnt actually say much in the autodocs, I assume that the 
metronome flag makes it like a real metronome, generating a signal at 
regular intervals.
  Fiddling about with the pl_Flags, I reset the `alarmset` bit..this just 
waits until the 1st second, then signals like there`s no tomorrow 
afterwards..ie about every 15/100ths of a second !

  I got a `bodged` workaround to work OK by incrementing the next alarmtime 
by 1200 (1 sec)and resetting the alarmset flag.
  I dunno, maybe its a bug in the library..I got V40.2, although every 
autodoc I`ve seen mentions V40.3, I checked my 0S3.5 and 3.9 CD`s and 
couldnt find a V40.3
Any ideas O`wise and knowledgable ones?


