@NODE "mail_279" " Re: SpecialInfo\Buffer "
From: David McMinn <dave@...>
Date: 11-01-01 22:46:44
Subject: @{b}Re: SpecialInfo\Buffer@{ub}

On 1 Nov 01, at 20:10, amorel broke out long enough to write:

> C=I think Fred's version (came with the NCS) is mostly OK except any
> C=structures which have unions in them. The original Acid amigalibs.res
> C=had some real bad bugs.
> 
> So the NCS one is the best to use? There`s also one from aminet. I don`t
> really know for sure which one I use(I think NCS). Don`t think it`s Acid`s
> as it has different names(like with underscores) in variables, than the
> official OS names.

That was done by Roger Beausoleil IIRC and only includes OS3.0. And IMHO 
it's a bit of hassle because of the underscores.

> And is there a fixed NCS one? Or any other?

AFAIK there is no fixed NCS one. But if you look at the OS includes, you do 
not see unions in the structures in many places. So it's safe enough to use 
it for most applications.

There are only really 3 versions:

The Acid version (has a few bugs)
Roger's version (amigalibsII, not sure if there are any bugs, maybe none, 
only does OS3.0 and below)
Fred's NCS version (has OS3.1 stuff and is most up to date)

The MUI resident files are all based on Fred's NCS amigalibs.res IIRC.

