@NODE "mail_292" " Re: the editor "
From: David McMinn <dave@...>
Date: 11-12-01 00:28:23
Subject: @{b}Re: the editor@{ub}

Hi amorel,

> Something which has been bugging me for a long time. Is there a way to
> continue a line in the blitz editor on a new line, without the compiler

Not AFAIK.

> thinking it`s garbage. I haven`t found one. For example if using wait_(1 LSL
> *w0\UserPort\mp_SigBit ....) when using like 5 windows you can see the line
> starts to become too long. And I don`t feel like making the command shorter by
> copying vars/pointers, if that`s even possible with wait_.

The only option is to use variables. I've had to do this a lot when using 
e.g. BltBitMapRastPort_ .... even with only small calculations in the 
parameters :)

Besides, assigning new variables on separate lines might help improve the 
readability of your code.

-- 
