@NODE "mail_295" " Tips for AB2 and Blitz working together "
From: Bernd Roesch <berndroesch1@...>
Date: 11-30-01 13:18:48
Subject: @{b}Tips for AB2 and Blitz working together@{ub}

Hi Stefano
Wy do you have in Blitz2 more objects as in Amiblitz ?
Do you use the same deflibs in BB2 and AB2 ?
What size have your deflibs now ?
Have you the same problems when you use the included deflibs in AB2 ?
Sure you have no double libs ?
DO you not use the same deflib for both
If this is reproducible all ok in Blitz2 send me your deflibs so i can look what happen
Normally the deflib size should not have more than 300kb

To All

AB2 can work together on same time with Blitz2.There is no need to use the new patchlibs or wizard/fpulib
if you dont want the additional Features.Also old Blitz2 work with the new patchlibs wizard/fpu without problem
(the optimizer the inline ppc/fpu dont work of course).If neither Blitz nor AB2 work when you installed the new libs
you maybee have libnums doubling 
You only need to put amiblitz2 and ped to your old Blitzinstall and all should work.If it work not so this seem a bug
in AB2.I have not change anything in the linker but maybee there can some problems happen.
If so ask me if you should send the deflibs to me maybee it helps to find a covert bug.    
   
