@NODE "mail_297" " tracker lib "
From: MadGun68 <madgun68@...>
Date: 11-10-01 01:05:19
Subject: @{b}tracker lib@{ub}

A question for any who might have used the ciatracker library.. Does the decodemodule function work for you?

Not sure off hand what the latest version spread around was, but in my source, the decode function wasn't working properly on my '060. It would work great if you had no fastram. :) 

Not having looked at the thing for several years, I have no idea if this is something that has always been present or something I introduced later on.

At any rate, I'll be releasing what I assume to be the last version of the library fairly soonish. Other than a couple of small fixes, it has a bunch of "toy" commands. (Stuff that seems cool at first, but has no real value to most people.) I suppose if you wanted to make your own protracker type program, it'd be perfect.

I just want to make an example program and maybe get the docs up to date first.

Steve
@ENDNODE

