@NODE "mail_318" " WinUAE & AMIthlon "
From: visionfx <visionfx@...>
Date: 11-19-01 03:28:09
Subject: @{b}WinUAE & AMIthlon@{ub}

Hi All Users,

Like I read sometimes on this list, some peoples use WinUAE or AMIthon to run Amiga... my question is, what is the difference between both emulators in pure speed? 

I bought an AMD Thunderbird 800 mhz for my family and I still have a very old A2000 ( And still love it too ) with 68040 33mhz. I hate Windows and like Amiga do not produce computers anymore... I would like to be able to run my programs on my PC if this worth it! And, are these emulators multitask?

Thx
Roger
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "mail_319" " Re: WinUAE & AMIthlon "
From: Thilo Köhler <koehlerthilo@...>
Date: 11-19-01 03:56:09
Subject: @{b}Re: WinUAE & AMIthlon@{ub}

Hello Roger!

> Like I read sometimes on this list, some peoples use WinUAE or AMIthon to
> run Amiga... my question is, what is the difference between both emulators
> in pure speed?
WinUAE runs under Windows and is slower. I does not make direct
use of the PC hardware, so things like Burning CDs are not possible
(yet). It makes use of the Windows driver so you have no problems
with available drivers. On the other hand you take all disadvantages
of windows with you, e.g. your "Amiga" can hang if there are page 
faults. This is because many people say it does not feel like an real 
Amiga. (I dont like especially the mouse, because it is emulated as
well and has big latency time). You can have it running in a window
under Windows. It emulates CustomChips, and is very kompatible
to old Games oder Demos. 
Amithlon uses a small Linux Kernel and runns as a single Linux task,
so it runns always smooth like a real Amiga. Most things have
their own driver, so you don`t have much choice which hardware
to use. But Amithlon is much faster, and you have a very direct
feeling like on a real Amiga. It doesnt emulate CustomChips,
so only OS-friendly software is running. I would call it a RTG-system
for the CPU.

From a mixture of benchmarks and subjective feeling I would say
Amithon is about 3-6 times faster than WinUAE-JIT looking at raw 
CPU speed, and especially disk access is very fast under Amithlon,
there is no emulation speed loss. It makes 5MB on my old 2GB
IDE drive on a PII300Mhz, taking full advantage of DMA.
(Windows says 4MB/s !).

For me Amithlon is the only choice, because I need speed for
up-to-date applications and no old games. But WinUAE will
be still much faster than a 68060 on your 800MHz Athlon,
but you can "smell" the underlying windows.

Hope this helps you a bit to see clearer.

Ciao,

Thilo


---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

