@NODE "mail_326" " Re: WinUAE & Debugger "
From: "DAVID MCMINN (9429210)" <9429210@...>
Date: 11-05-01 16:00:20
Subject: @{b}Re: WinUAE & Debugger@{ub}

> > And have you tried running Snoopdos before you compile and run your
> > program? It may show the debugger failing to load something.
> >
> I checked that and found a missing "camd.library" ?

Strange, I just tried to compile a "Hello world" type program and never
had any reference to that library. I'm using REDDebugger v2.52, and it
definately works OK here.

Maybe you could try re-installing the BSS (I guess that's the debugger
you use - I can't remember if you said which one)? It should install all
the files it requires if that's the problem.


You could also try to make sure you have the following:

An assign called Blitz2: to the correct drawer
The file blitz2:defaultdbug (384 bytes for BSS version)
The file blitz2:dbug/reddebugger (185720 bytes for v2.52)

You might also need RexxMast running.

Oh, and I guess you could try deleting the file envarc:bb_dbug.prefs to
try to get the debugger to return to it's default setup.

