@NODE "mail_329" " Re: WinUAE & EOF() "
From: Tony Rolfe <edgewater@...>
Date: 11-08-01 22:36:08
Subject: @{b}Re: WinUAE & EOF()@{ub}

On 8 Nov 2001, at 17:52, Thilo Köhler wrote:

> Anyone noticed that EOF(#file) does not work
> under WinUAE ? It always give "False" back,
> even if the file is at the end. Is there a workaround ?

It's a known bug.  Try 

While Loc(File#) <> Lof(File#)
	do stuff here
wend

